                     <note>- The correct order of fols. containing Texts I-IV is as follows:</note>
                     <note>1 Peter</note>
                     <note>1:1-17 (<locus target="6rv">6rv</locus>); 1:17-2:7 (<locus target="17rv">17rv</locus>); 2:7-20 (<locus target="12rv">12rv</locus>); 2:20-3:9 (<locus target="18rv">18rv</locus>); 3:9-22 (<locus target="23rv">23rv</locus>); 4:1-14 (<locus target="13rv">13rv</locus>); 5:11-14 (<locus target="8ra">8ra-</locus>b)</note>
                     <note>2 Peter</note>
                     <note>1:1-9 (<locus target="8rb">8rb-</locus>vb); 1:10-21 (<locus target="24rv">24rv</locus>); 1:21-3:4 (<locus from="19r" to="20v">19r-20v</locus>); 3:4-18 (<locus target="11rv">11rv</locus>)</note>
                     <note>1 John</note>
                     <note>1:1-2:23 (<locus from="9ra" to="10vb">9ra-10vb</locus>); 2:24-4:17 (<locus from="14ra" to="16vb">14ra-16vb</locus>); 4:17-5:20 (<locus from="21ra" to="22vb">21ra-22vb</locus>)</note>
                     <note>2 John</note>
                     <note>1:1-4 (<locus target="22vb">22vb</locus>); 1:4-13 (<locus target="25ra">25ra-</locus>va).</note>
                     <note>-Text VIII is divided into 63 "sections" (kǝfl).</note>
                     <note>-In a few fols. the word qum "stop", "stand" (<locus target="15rb">15rb</locus>, 28ra 48ra), frequently in abbreviated form (ቁ፡) by a crude secondary hand, is written interlineally or in the margins throughout the Ms.</note>
